Top Turkish club, Besiktas is interested in signing striker Paul Onuachu to boost it firepower. New coach, Valerien Ismael has pinpointed Genk striker, Onuachu as a top target for the Istanbul giant, according to Fotomac. The transfer market value of the Super Eagles striker is put at 17 Million Euros. He cost his Belgian club a bargain six Million Euros in 2019. Onuachu has been linked with several top European clubs including Atletico Madrid, Lazio and Fiorentina. Last season, Onuachu, 28, netted 23 goals and provided three assists in 43 appearances. This was after he finished as Goal King of Belgium the previous season and many had expected him to make a big transfer.